cocus#Workshop: The parent of Thing is the Workshop which is the child of the Workshop.
cocus#Event: Event Setup is the parent of Thing and Email Template. It is the parent of Event Tracks which is the parent of Event Setup.
cocus#Account: Administrator is the parent of Person who is the child of the Administrator. The Administrator is the parent of Thing and is assigned the role of the parent of the Account which was modified by the Administrator. The Account was registrated by the Administrator.
cocus#Inforamtion: The following table shows the percentage of people who are enrolled in the program.
cocus#User: The user is the child of the Committee and the parent of the user. The user is the inverse of add and is the child of the Committee.
cocus#Role: The Administrator is the parent of Thing and the child of the Administrator.
cocus#Help_Request: Help Request is the parent of Help Request.
cocus#Person: The person is the parent of Thing and is the child of the Administrator.
cocus#Symposium: Approval Email is the parent email of the Symposium which is a child of the Symposium. Approval Email is also the parent email of Group Email which is received by a person.
cocus#Abstract: Abstract is the parent of Paper which is also the child of Invited Paper.
cocus#Paper: The Corresponding Author is the parent of the document submitted by the Corresponding Author. The Author is the child of the Corresponding Author.
cocus#Administrator: The Administrator is the parent of the Administrator who adds the role of the Reviewer Role. The Reviewer Role is the child of the parent of Thing. The Account is registrated by the Administrator who is the parent of the Administrator.
cocus#Document: The document is a child of the person who is the parent of Thing. The document is also the child of the person who is the administrator. The administrator is the parent of the person who is assigned the role of the administrator.
cocus#Invited_Paper: The Corresponding Author is the parent of the Paper which was submitted by the Corresponding Author. The Author is the parent of the User and the Author is the parent of the Invited Paper.
cocus#Admin_Role: Admin Role is the parent of Thing and is child of Admin Role.
cocus#Paper_Typologies: Paper Typologies is the parent of Event Setup which is a concomitant of Event Tracks and Thing.
cocus#Event_Setup: Event Setup is a child of Event Tracks which is parented by Review Form. Review Form is also the child of Preview which is the parent of Review Form.
cocus#Event_URL: The event URL is the parent of the event URL.
cocus#URL: The event URL is the child of the event URL and the parent of the URL.
cocus#Notification_Email: The Notification Email is the parent of the Document which is submitted by the user. The Document is also the parent of the Document which is used by the Committee.
cocus#Email: The User is the child of the Administrator who is the parent of the Committee. The Administrator is the parent of the User who receives the Approval email. The Approval email was received by the User and the Committee is the parent of the User.
cocus#Short_Paper: Short Paper is the parent of Document which was created by a person who is the child of the Administrator. Paper is also the child of Document which was created by a person who is the parent of Paper.
cocus#Author_Role: The author Role is the parent of Thing and Committe Role.
cocus#Preview: Review Form is the parent of Preview and Event Setup. Submission Template is the parent of Event Setup which was confirmed by Approval Email. Thing is the parent of Event Setup.
cocus#Review_Form: Review Form is the parent of Conference and Thing. It is also the parent of Event Setup which is the parent of Review Form.
cocus#Review: Review is the parent of Document which is the parent of Thing.
cocus#Committe_Role: The Committe Role is the parent of the Admin Role which is the child of Thing.
cocus#Group_Email: Approval Email is the parent email of Group Email. It is also the parent email of Notification Email which is the parent email of Approval Email. Email is also the parent email of Conference and Thing.
cocus#Submission_Template: The Submission Template is the parent of the Event Setup, which is a child of Event Tracks. Approval Email is the parent of the Event Setup, which is also the parent of Thing.
cocus#Review_Form_Setup: Review Form Setup is the parent of Review Form and Preview.
cocus#Misc: Feature Request is a child of Help Request which is parented by Feature Request. This activity has resulted in a document.
cocus#Author: The author of the document is the parent of the user who is the child of the Committee which is the parent of the document. The document is also the parent of Thing and the document is also the parent of Document.
cocus#Event_Creation: Event Creation is the parent of Document which is the parent of Thing. Submission is the parent of Document which was created and has resulted in a Document.
cocus#Approval_Email: Rejection Email is a document created by a person and received by a user. The email is parented by the Administrator and the user. The user is the child of the Author and the Approval Email.
cocus#Rejection_Email: Rejection Email is received by a person who is the parent of the email. Administrator is the parent of the person who created the event. User is the child of the Administrator who is the parent of the person who created the event.
cocus#Submission: Documents are received by the user via email. Documents are submitted by the user via email. Documents are parented by the user and the committee.
cocus#Template: The person is the parent of the document which is the parent of Thing. The template is used by the person.
cocus#Feature_Request: Feature Request is a child of Misc and is parent of the Help Request. This activity has resulted in a document.
cocus#Committee: Corresponding Author is the parent of the User who is the child of the Author and the Committee. The Author is the child of the Corresponding Author and the Committee is the parent of the User.
cocus#Event_Tracks: Paper Typologies is the parent of Event Setup which is the parent of Event Tracks. Paper Typologies is the parent of Event Setup which is a research topic.
cocus#Request: Event Approval is a parent of Activity which is child of Request. It has resulted in an Approval Email which confirms the event.
cocus#Activity: The Author is the parent of the Person who is the inverse of add. The Author is the parent of the Person who is the parent of the Thing. The Author is the parent of the Person who is the child of the Activity which is the child of the Registration. The Registration has resulted in a rejection email.
cocus#Head_Role: The Head Role is the parent of the Administrator who is the parent of the Reviewer Role. The Administrator is the parent of the Person who is the inverse of add and remove.
cocus#Detail: Detail is the parent of Thing.
cocus#Corresponding_Author: The Corresponding Author is the parent of the User and the Corresponding Author is the parent of the Thing. The Administrator is the child of the Corresponding Author.
cocus#Reviewer_Role: Reviewer Role is assigned by Administrator. Administrator is the parent of the Head Role. The Administrator is the parent of the person who is responsible for the event approval of a Thing. The Event Approval has resulted in an Approval Email.
cocus#Event_Approval: The Author and the User are both children of the person who is the parent of the person who is the child of the event set up. The event is defined by the Event Approval email and is the parent of the Review Form and the Research Topic. The User is the child of the Author and the Help Request is the child of the Person who is the parent of the person who is the child of the Event Approval email.
cocus#Registration: The User is the parent of the person who registered. The User is the child of the Committee which is the parent of the User. Registration has resulted in the User being the child of the Committee.
cocus#Full_Paper: The full paper is the parent of the document which was submitted by the user. The document is also the child of the Invited Paper which was submitted by the user. The Committee is the parent of the document which was submitted by the user.
cocus#Research_Topic: The Research Topic is the parent of the Event Setup which is created by a person and removed by a person. The Submission Template is the parent of the Event which is created by a person and is the parent of the Thing.
cocus#Description: The following table shows the percentage of people who are enrolled in the program.
cocus#Conference: The Event Tracks is the parent of the Conference and the Event Setup. The Event Tracks is the child of the Event Tracks.
cocus#Assistance: The parent of the Help Request is the parent of the Help Request which is sent by a person and is also the child of the Registration activity.
cocus#Email_Template: The email template is the parent of Event Setup which is the event that is the parent of Thing and Symposium. The event is also the parent of the Submission Template which is the event's parent.
